	SingletonNode
{%- endblock %}
{% block content %}

<p>Singleton Nodes are node types, where only 1 instance is allowed per graph. This single instance is always reachable through the anchor node with the get_irg_XX() functions. There exist new_XX() functions for singleton nodes too, but they just return the single instance after each call.
</p>
{% endblock %}
